				\begin{document}$$E_{itp}^0(Y_{it},L_{it},e_{itp}(Y_{it}/L_{it})) = e_{itp}(Y_{it}/L_{it})\cdot Y_{it}.$$\end{document}Eitp0(Yit,Lit,eitp(Yit∕Lit))=eitp(Yit∕Lit)⋅Yit.The emission intensity is region (i), time (t), and pollutant (p) specific and characteristically depends on the per capita income level of the region, defined above as the GDP, Y, divided by the population, L. GDP is endogenously determined in RICE while population is exogenous, taking the medium variant estimate of the 2017 version of the UN Population Prospects through 210041, and remaining constant thereafter.

