We fit a simple linear regression line through the multiple estimates of κ for each SSP, constrained to begin at the origin, and take the slope of that line as our estimate (Supplementary Fig. 6). We derive five estimates of κ (one for each SSP) for each region-pollutant pair, using the middle-of-the-road SSP2 as our standard case, with the alternative SSPs tested in sensitivity analyses. The total post-mitigation level of emissions is therefore:7\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
