The TM5-FASST interface allows the 56 source regions to be aggregated into larger regions that approximate the RICE regions. Due to the size of the RICE regions, we assume that the change in exposure to PM2.5, ΔC, in region i depends only on the change in emissions within that same region (i') and that the change is estimated via the SRM (SR) that encodes atmospheric transport. We also assume that the SRM does not change over time and that changes in the three precursor pollutants are additive:8\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
