Changes in air quality are monetized as the health co-benefit, B, by multiplying the number of life years gained by the value of a life-year (VOLY). We follow the same approach taken in early versions of RICE’s climate damage function where a VOLY is assumed to equal 2 years of regional per capita consumption, c39:23\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
